name: Tah'i H
text: Alfredo is always overcooked and pasta is crunchy, very little to almost no sauce. Always a long wait time even when no customers. Staff is always friendly but could do a better job.

name: Daniel Barajas
text: Food was 30 minutes late and over cooked, my pizza was way too crunchy, the cheese was so over cooked it had no flavor. Do not recommend this place at all.

name: vernon beavers
text: Pizza was hot crisp crust plenty of sauce staff was friendly not busy

name: Mike Ulloa
text: If you're just looking for something to fill your stomach that meets the bare minimum of being able to be called a pizza, then this is your place.

name: Christian Vasquez
text: The employees couldn't find the street after address checking for it. Domino's delivers to the same place just fine. Upsetting because I love Pizza hut but the employees can't address check or use Google maps correctly

name: Misha Slavin
text: Surprisingly fast to order from here on a Friday night (like 15 minutes) and everything was cooked exactly how I expected it to be. Giving 5 stars because it was probably the easiest fastest Pizza hut experience I've had.

name: William Shields
text: Prices high, but solid pizza and fast service
